      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-5', question: "She has been working here ___ three years.", questionZh: "她在这里工作已经三年了___。", options: ["for", "since", "in", "over"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "for duration period" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-6', question: "The new policy will ___ everyone in the company.", questionZh: "新政策将影响公司里的每个人___。", options: ["affect", "effect", "effective", "efficiently"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "affect = influence verb form" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-7', question: "If I had ___ more time, I would have finished the project.", questionZh: "如果我有更多时间，我就已经完成了项目___。", options: ["had", "have", "having", "to have"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "if had done past unreal" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-8', question: "The lecture was both ___ and interesting.", questionZh: "这次讲座既又很有趣___。", options: ["informative", "boring", "difficult", "short"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "both and = two things together" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-9', question: "I suggest that we ___ the meeting until next week.", questionZh: "我建议我们把会议推迟到下周___。", options: ["postpone", "postpones", "postponing", "to postpone"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "suggest should do subjunctive" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-10', question: "He acted as if he ___ the owner of the company.", questionZh: "他表现得就好像他是公司的主人一样___。", options: ["were", "is", "was", "be"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "as if were subjunctive mood" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-11', question: "The book, ___ cover is damaged, belongs to me.", questionZh: "那本封面坏了的书属于我___。", options: ["whose", "which", "that", "its"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "whose = possessive books cover" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-12', question: "Only when you finish your homework ___ watch TV.", questionZh: "只有当你完成作业，你才能看电视___。", options: ["can you", "you can", "could you", "you could"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "only adverbial triggers inversion" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-13', question: "I would rather you ___ tomorrow.", questionZh: "我宁愿你明天来___。", options: ["come", "came", "to come", "coming"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "would rather sb do base form" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-14', question: "The issue is still ___ discussion.", questionZh: "这个问题仍在讨论中___。", options: ["under", "in", "on", "at"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "under discussion = in process" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-15', question: "She insists that she ___ the truth.", questionZh: "她坚持说她说的是真话话___。", options: ["tell", "tells", "told", "telling"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "insists that should do subjunctive after insist" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-16', question: "The harder you work, ___ results you will achieve.", questionZh: "你越努力工作，你取得更好的成绩___。", options: ["the better", "the best", "better", "more better"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "the comparative the comparative" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-17', question: "It is important that everyone ___ on time.", questionZh: "每个人准时是很重要的___。", options: ["be", "is", "was", "to be"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "important should do subjunctive" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-18', question: "By the time the manager arrives, the report will have been ___.", questionZh: "到经理到达时，报告就准备好了___。", options: ["prepared", "preparing", "prepare", "to prepare"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "by future = fut perfect passive" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-19', question: "He did not notice the teacher ___ behind him.", questionZh: "他没有注意到老师站在他身后___。", options: ["standing", "stood", "to stand", "stand"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "notice sb doing observed in progress" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-20', question: "The building whose ___ are broken is under repair.", questionZh: "窗户坏了的那座建筑正在维修中___。", options: ["windows", "doors", "roofs", "walls"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "whose = possessive buildings windows" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-21', question: "I would appreciate it ___ if you could reply soon.", questionZh: "如果你能尽快回复，我将非常感激___。", options: ["very much", "that", "this", "much"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "I would appreciate it if" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-22', question: "No matter ___ hard he tried, he failed.", questionZh: "无论他多努力，他都失败了___。", options: ["how", "what", "which", "when"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "no matter how adj adverb" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-23', question: "The man whom we ___ yesterday is a scientist.", questionZh: "昨天我们拜访的那个人是位科学家___。", options: ["visited", "see", "met", "knew"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "whom = object form we visited whom" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-24', question: "It was not until yesterday that ___ the truth.", questionZh: "直到昨天我才了解真相___。", options: ["I realized", "he realized", "she realized", "we realized"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "not until强调句 It was not until that" },
      { id: 'cet4-2024-6-25', question: "She speaks English as if she ___ a native speaker.", questionZh: "她说英语就好像她是母语者一样___。", options: ["were", "is", "was", "has been"], correctAnswer: 0, explanation: "as if were unreal subjunctive" }
